    OpenGL 1.2.1 Sample Implementation Release Notes

    Last modified August 4, 2000

Most Recent Changes:

  - Bug fixes in the build structure, GLU and GLW libraries, and 
    integration testing against XFree86 3.3.6.

Open Issues:

  - GLX 1.3 protocol for OpenGL 1.2 and ARB_multitexture exists, but the
    new GLX 1.3 APIs (pbuffers, make current read, etc.) are not
    provided yet.

  - Implementation support for XFree86 4.0.

  - Support for newly approved ARB extensions.
